steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9pb8i","text":"Streak out the plasmid parts that will be used in the assembly onto LB agar plates with the appropriate antibiotics (Chloramphenicol 100µg/mL for Type 1-7 parts; Kanamycin or Gentamicin 100µg/mL for Type 8 backbone parts). Incubate overnight at 37ºC. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f25cl","text":"Inoculate a single colony into 25mL of LB plus antibiotics in the late afternoon/early evening. Incubate overnight at 37ºC while shaking at 200rpm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4lnjp","text":"Spin the culture at 5000g for 20 minutes. Remove the supernatant, resuspend the pellet in 1mL water. Perform a plasmid miniprep (Zyppy miniprep or Omega E.Z.N.A. Plasmid Mini Kit II) following the standard kit protocols. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5ngav","text":"Dilute 2x or electroporate 2µL of the GGA directly into electrocompetent cells (i.e. SM10pir, S17pir). Recover 1+ hours and plate on LB Agar media containing the correct antibiotic concentrations. Incubate at 37ºC overnight. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":89,"length":3},{"style":"italic","offset":97,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6pb5i","text":"Screen colonies for correct insert and perform colony PCR with primers spanning assembly junctions. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"202i2","text":"Streak out clones that yield a band onto LB Agar media containing the correct antibiotic concentrations and incubate at 37ºC overnight. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ablu8","text":"Inoculate a single colony into 25mL LB broth containing the correct antibiotic concentrations and incubate at 37ºC overnight. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fafmg","text":"Store overnight culture in cryovials for long term storage. Add 500µL of culture to 500µL of 50% glycerol and store in -80ºC freezer. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"306ij","text":"With remaining culture, Centrifuge at 5000g for 20 minutes. Remove the supernatant, resuspend the pellet in 1mL water. Perform a plasmid miniprep (Zyppy miniprep or Omega E.Z.N.A. Plasmid Mini Kit II) following the standard kit protocol. Elute with water. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cabd","text":"Measure the Plasmid DNA concentration on a spectrophotometer. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a557m","text":"Send the miniprepped plasmid for Sanger or Oxford Nanopore long-read plasmid sequencing to confirm the construct. Store the remaining miniprep for downstream applications (i.e. shuttle into different electrocompetent cell for conjugation). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
